# Add or Clarify Scenarios

**Target:** {{ feature_path }}
{% if rule_name %}**Focus Rule:** {{ rule_name }}{% endif %}

## What To Do

Add scenarios to rules that lack coverage. Read the feature file's NORMATIVE CONTRACT MIRROR header for requirements.
If new step phrases are required, add them — Tesaki will automatically follow up with CreateMissingBindings.
Prefer existing step phrases where possible to minimize new bindings.

## Constraints (MUST NOT VIOLATE)

- Do NOT add new `Rule:` blocks — only add Scenarios under existing Rules.
- Do NOT modify the Feature description or existing Rule text.
- Validation will reject changes if the rule count increases.
- You MUST increase executable scenarios by at least one. Promoting a @Deferred scenario counts.
- It is OK if lint fails due to missing bindings; that is expected and will be handled next.
- New scenarios must add a distinct "Then" outcome (not just repeating the same Then set or only adding "no panic occurs").
- If a rule has only `@Deferred` scenarios, promote at least one by removing `@Deferred` (preferred to adding new scenarios).
- If any promotion candidate requires zero new step texts, prefer promoting one of those and avoid introducing new step phrases.

